---
import DocsLayout from "../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout title="Guided Tutorials" description="Step-by-step walk-throughs for practical engineering and physics applications" activeSection="tutorials">
  <div class="page-header">
    <div class="kicker">Guides</div>
    <h1>Tutorials</h1>
    <p>Step-by-step wizard walk-throughs solving complex engineering, calibration, and orbital mechanics problems using physure.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- Wizard Interface -->
  <div class="tutorial-wizard">
    <!-- Wizard Sidebar: Choose Tutorial -->
    <div class="wizard-selector">
      <button class="t-select-btn active" data-tutorial="sensor">🌡️ Sensor Calibration</button>
      <button class="t-select-btn" data-tutorial="orbital">🌌 Kepler Orbit Solver</button>
      <button class="t-select-btn" data-tutorial="fluid">💧 Bernoulli Pipe Flow</button>
    </div>

    <!-- Wizard Content Box -->
    <div class="wizard-box">
      <!-- Sensor Calibration Tutorial -->
      <div class="tutorial-content active" id="sensorTutorial">
        <div class="wizard-step-header">
          <h2>Sensor Calibration & Offset Conversion</h2>
          <div class="step-dots">
            <span class="step-dot active" data-step="1">1</span>
            <span class="step-dot" data-step="2">2</span>
            <span class="step-dot" data-step="3">3</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 1 -->
        <div class="step-pane active" data-step="1">
          <h3>Step 1: Input Raw Readings and Uncertainty</h3>
          <p>
            In sensor calibration, we start with raw measurements and standard deviations. Since temperature scales are offset scales, we must be careful with Celsius and Fahrenheit.
          </p>
          <pre><code>from physure import Q_

# Raw reading at ice point (Celsius offset scale)
t_raw = Q_(0.15, "degC", uncertainty=0.05)

# Expected reference value (absolute Kelvin scale)
t_ref = Q_(273.15, "K")

print("Raw reading:", t_raw)
print("Reference:", t_ref)</code></pre>
          <div class="wizard-nav">
            <button class="btn-primary next-step-btn">Next Step →</button>
            <a href="/playground" class="btn-secondary run-in-playground" style="margin-left:auto;">Run this step 🚀</a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 2 -->
        <div class="step-pane" data-step="2">
          <h3>Step 2: Compute Offset Error (Absolute to Delta Conversion)</h3>
          <p>
            Subtracting the raw value from the reference computes the offset. Subtracting two absolute temperatures automatically returns a **Delta** unit (difference) to preserve thermodynamic meaning:
          </p>
          <pre><code># Convert raw to Kelvin to subtract absolute temperatures
t_raw_k = t_raw.to("K")

# Difference returns delta units (e.g. delta_degC or K)
t_offset = t_ref - t_raw_k

print("Raw in Kelvin:", t_raw_k)
print("Calibration Offset:", t_offset)  # Result: ~0.0 ± 0.05 K</code></pre>
          <div class="wizard-nav">
            <button class="btn-secondary prev-step-btn">← Previous</button>
            <button class="btn-primary next-step-btn">Next Step →</button>
            <a href="/playground" class="btn-secondary run-in-playground" style="margin-left:auto;">Run this step 🚀</a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 3 -->
        <div class="step-pane" data-step="3">
          <h3>Step 3: Calibrate New Readings and Convert to Fahrenheit</h3>
          <p>
            Apply the calibration offset to a new sensor reading. Finally, convert the calibrated absolute temperature to Fahrenheit:
          </p>
          <pre><code># New sensor reading
t_new = Q_(25.4, "degC", uncertainty=0.1)

# Apply delta offset (absolute + delta -> absolute)
t_calibrated = t_new + t_offset.to("delta_degC")

# Convert absolute Kelvin/Celsius to Fahrenheit
t_fahrenheit = t_calibrated.to("degF")

print("Calibrated Temp (C):", t_calibrated)
print("Calibrated Temp (F):", t_fahrenheit)
# Output: ~77.72 ± 0.20 degF</code></pre>
          <div class="callout callout-success">
            <p><strong>Success:</strong> You have calibrated a sensor and propagated error across offset scale systems!</p>
          </div>
          <div class="wizard-nav">
            <button class="btn-secondary prev-step-btn">← Previous</button>
            <a href="/playground" class="btn-primary run-in-playground">Try in Playground 🚀</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Kepler Orbit Solver -->
      <div class="tutorial-content" id="orbitalTutorial">
        <div class="wizard-step-header">
          <h2>🌌 Astrophysics: Keplerian Orbit Solver</h2>
          <div class="step-dots">
            <span class="step-dot active" data-step="1">1</span>
            <span class="step-dot" data-step="2">2</span>
            <span class="step-dot" data-step="3">3</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 1 -->
        <div class="step-pane active" data-step="1">
          <h3>Step 1: Define Constants and Astronomical Parameters</h3>
          <p>
            Calculate the orbital period of Earth around the Sun using Kepler's Third Law: <code>T² = 4π²r³ / (G × M)</code>. We start by gathering physical constants:
          </p>
          <pre><code>import math
from physure import Q_
from physure.constants import G  # Gravitational constant

# Mass of the Sun
M_sun = Q_(1.989e30, "kg", uncertainty=1e26)

# Earth orbital radius (1 Astronomical Unit)
r_orbit = Q_(1.496e11, "m", uncertainty=1e7)

print("G:", G)
print("M_sun:", M_sun)
print("Radius:", r_orbit)</code></pre>
          <div class="wizard-nav">
            <button class="btn-primary next-step-btn">Next Step →</button>
            <a href="/playground" class="btn-secondary run-in-playground" style="margin-left:auto;">Run this step 🚀</a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 2 -->
        <div class="step-pane" data-step="2">
          <h3>Step 2: Solve Kepler's Equation</h3>
          <p>
            Calculate the square of the orbital period. Units are automatically multiplied and divided, proving dimensional consistency:
          </p>
          <pre><code># Kepler's Third Law formula
T_squared = (4 * (math.pi**2) * (r_orbit**3)) / (G * M_sun)

# Take the square root to get the period T
T = T_squared ** 0.5

print("T² units:", T_squared.unit)  # s^2
print("Orbital Period T:", T)        # ~3.155e7 s</code></pre>
          <div class="wizard-nav">
            <button class="btn-secondary prev-step-btn">← Previous</button>
            <button class="btn-primary next-step-btn">Next Step →</button>
            <a href="/playground" class="btn-secondary run-in-playground" style="margin-left:auto;">Run this step 🚀</a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 3 -->
        <div class="step-pane" data-step="3">
          <h3>Step 3: Convert to Years and Analyze Error</h3>
          <p>
            Convert seconds to solar years. The uncertainty of the orbital period is automatically computed from the Sun's mass and orbital radius margins:
          </p>
          <pre><code># Convert seconds to years
T_years = T.to("yr")

print(f"Orbital Period: &#123;T_years.magnitude:.4f&#125; ± &#123;T_years.uncertainty:.4f&#125; years")
# Output: 1.0001 ± 0.0001 years

# Relative precision of calculations
relative_err = (T_years.uncertainty / T_years.magnitude) * 100
print(f"Calculation margin of error: &#123;relative_err:.6f&#125;%")</code></pre>
          <div class="callout callout-info">
            <p>The uncertainty propagates through gravity and orbital bounds automatically without manual partial derivatives!</p>
          </div>
          <div class="wizard-nav">
            <button class="btn-secondary prev-step-btn">← Previous</button>
            <a href="/playground" class="btn-primary run-in-playground">Try in Playground 🚀</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Bernoulli Pipe Flow -->
      <div class="tutorial-content" id="fluidTutorial">
        <div class="wizard-step-header">
          <h2>💧 Fluid Dynamics: Pipe Flow Drop</h2>
          <div class="step-dots">
            <span class="step-dot active" data-step="1">1</span>
            <span class="step-dot" data-step="2">2</span>
            <span class="step-dot" data-step="3">3</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 1 -->
        <div class="step-pane active" data-step="1">
          <h3>Step 1: Set Up Pipe Velocities</h3>
          <p>
            Analyze pressure drop in a contracting horizontal water pipe using Bernoulli's principle: <code>P₁ - P₂ = ½ρ(v₂² - v₁²)</code>. Start by setting inlet/outlet velocities:
          </p>
          <pre><code>from physure import Q_

# Water Density
rho = Q_(997, "kg/m^3")

# Inlet velocity (wide pipe)
v1 = Q_(1.2, "m/s", uncertainty=0.02)

# Outlet velocity (contracted pipe)
v2 = Q_(4.5, "m/s", uncertainty=0.05)

print("Density:", rho)
print("V1:", v1)
print("V2:", v2)</code></pre>
          <div class="wizard-nav">
            <button class="btn-primary next-step-btn">Next Step →</button>
            <a href="/playground" class="btn-secondary run-in-playground" style="margin-left:auto;">Run this step 🚀</a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 2 -->
        <div class="step-pane" data-step="2">
          <h3>Step 2: Solve Pressure Drop</h3>
          <p>
            Evaluate the pressure difference. Dynamic velocity pressures automatically combine with fluid density to resolve to Pascal (Pa):
          </p>
          <pre><code># Bernoulli equation for horizontal pipe
pressure_drop = 0.5 * rho * (v2**2 - v1**2)

print("Pressure Drop:", pressure_drop)
print("Units resolved:", pressure_drop.unit)  # Pa
# Result: ~9376.78 Pa</code></pre>
          <div class="wizard-nav">
            <button class="btn-secondary prev-step-btn">← Previous</button>
            <button class="btn-primary next-step-btn">Next Step →</button>
            <a href="/playground" class="btn-secondary run-in-playground" style="margin-left:auto;">Run this step 🚀</a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 3 -->
        <div class="step-pane" data-step="3">
          <h3>Step 3: Convert to Bar and Propagate Error</h3>
          <p>
            Convert the pressure difference to bar or psi. The standard deviations on water velocities propagate into the final pressure margin:
          </p>
          <pre><code># Conversions
drop_bar = pressure_drop.to("bar")
drop_psi = pressure_drop.to("psi")

print(f"Drop in bar: &#123;drop_bar.magnitude:.4f&#125; ± &#123;drop_bar.uncertainty:.4f&#125; bar")
# ~0.0938 ± 0.0022 bar

print(f"Drop in psi: &#123;drop_psi.magnitude:.4f&#125; ± &#123;drop_psi.uncertainty:.4f&#125; psi")
# ~1.3600 ± 0.0322 psi</code></pre>
          <div class="wizard-nav">
            <button class="btn-secondary prev-step-btn">← Previous</button>
            <a href="/playground" class="btn-primary run-in-playground">Try in Playground 🚀</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <script is:inline>
    // Handles changing tutorial selection
    document.querySelectorAll('.t-select-btn').forEach(btn => {
      btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
        // Toggle selected button state
        document.querySelectorAll('.t-select-btn').forEach(b => b.classList.remove('active'));
        btn.classList.add('active');

        // Toggle selected tutorial contents
        const target = btn.getAttribute('data-tutorial');
        document.querySelectorAll('.tutorial-content').forEach(c => c.classList.remove('active'));
        
        if (target === 'sensor') {
          document.getElementById('sensorTutorial').classList.add('active');
        } else if (target === 'orbital') {
          document.getElementById('orbitalTutorial').classList.add('active');
        } else if (target === 'fluid') {
          document.getElementById('fluidTutorial').classList.add('active');
        }
      });
    });

    // Handles changing steps inside a tutorial
    document.querySelectorAll('.tutorial-content').forEach(tut => {
      const stepPanes = tut.querySelectorAll('.step-pane');
      const dots = tut.querySelectorAll('.step-dot');

      function showStep(stepNum) {
        stepPanes.forEach(p => p.classList.toggle('active', parseInt(p.getAttribute('data-step')) === stepNum));
        dots.forEach(d => d.classList.toggle('active', parseInt(d.getAttribute('data-step')) === stepNum));
      }

      tut.querySelectorAll('.next-step-btn').forEach(btn => {
        btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
          const currentActive = tut.querySelector('.step-pane.active');
          const currentStep = parseInt(currentActive.getAttribute('data-step'));
          showStep(currentStep + 1);
        });
      });

      tut.querySelectorAll('.prev-step-btn').forEach(btn => {
        btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
          const currentActive = tut.querySelector('.step-pane.active');
          const currentStep = parseInt(currentActive.getAttribute('data-step'));
          showStep(currentStep - 1);
        });
      });

      dots.forEach(dot => {
        dot.addEventListener('click', () => {
          showStep(parseInt(dot.getAttribute('data-step')));
        });
      });
    });

    // Check URL parameters on load to restore state (resuming tutorial)
    const urlParams = new URLSearchParams(window.location.search);
    const paramTutorial = urlParams.get('tutorial');
    const paramStep = parseInt(urlParams.get('step'));

    if (paramTutorial) {
      const tabBtn = document.querySelector(`.t-select-btn[data-tutorial="${paramTutorial}"]`);
      if (tabBtn) {
        tabBtn.click();
      }
    }
    
    if (paramStep) {
      const activeTut = document.querySelector('.tutorial-content.active');
      if (activeTut) {
        const dots = activeTut.querySelectorAll('.step-dot');
        const dot = Array.from(dots).find(d => parseInt(d.getAttribute('data-step')) === paramStep);
        if (dot) {
          dot.click();
        }
      }
    }
  </script>
</DocsLayout>

<style>
  .tutorial-wizard {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }
  
  /* Wizard Sidebar */
  .wizard-selector {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    width: 240px;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .t-select-btn {
    text-align: left;
    background: var(--panel);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    color: var(--text2);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 550;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 0.2s;
  }
  .t-select-btn:hover {
    background: var(--panel2);
    color: var(--text);
  }
  .t-select-btn.active {
    background: var(--accent-glow);
    border-color: var(--accent);
    color: var(--accent2);
  }

  /* Content box */
  .wizard-box {
    flex: 1;
    background: var(--panel);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: 2rem;
    min-height: 480px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }
  
  .tutorial-content {
    display: none;
    flex-direction: column;
    height: 100%;
  }
  .tutorial-content.active {
    display: flex;
  }

  /* Step dots indicator */
  .wizard-step-header {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border2);
    padding-bottom: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  .wizard-step-header h2 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin: 0;
    border: none;
    padding: 0;
  }
  .step-dots {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }
  .step-dot {
    width: 24px;
    height: 24px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--panel2);
    border: 1px solid var(--border2);
    color: var(--text3);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 0.15s;
  }
  .step-dot.active {
    background: var(--accent);
    border-color: var(--accent);
    color: white;
  }

  /* Step panes */
  .step-pane {
    display: none;
    flex-direction: column;
    height: 100%;
  }
  .step-pane.active {
    display: flex;
  }
  .step-pane h3 {
    margin-top: 0;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }
  .step-pane p {
    font-size: 0.925rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  /* Wizard Navigation Buttons */
  .wizard-nav {
    margin-top: auto;
    padding-top: 1.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border2);
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }
  
  .btn-primary {
    background: var(--accent);
    color: white;
    padding: 0.55rem 1.25rem;
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    border: none;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    cursor: pointer;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: background 0.15s;
  }
  .btn-primary:hover {
    background: var(--accent2);
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  
  .btn-secondary {
    background: var(--panel2);
    border: 1px solid var(--border2);
    color: var(--text2);
    padding: 0.55rem 1.25rem;
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 0.15s;
  }
  .btn-secondary:hover {
    border-color: var(--accent);
    color: var(--text);
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .tutorial-wizard {
      flex-direction: column;
    }
    .wizard-selector {
      width: 100%;
      flex-direction: row;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
    }
    .t-select-btn {
      flex: 1;
      min-width: 150px;
    }
  }
</style>
